"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["#!pip install optuna\n","\n","import optuna"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"53f40c6c","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.005275,"end_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.371417+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.366142+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["**Optuna** is a tool used to **automatically find the best hyperparameters** for machine learning models.\n","### Simple Idea\n","Instead of manually trying different settings, Optuna:\n","- Tries many combinations\n","- Learns from past trials\n","- Finds the best settings faster\n","\n","### Key Features\n","- **Automatic tuning** of hyperparameters  \n","- **Efficient search** (tries smart combinations)  \n","- **Pruning** → stops bad trials early to save time  \n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"874edefb","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.005141,"end_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.38188+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.376739+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Optuna Objective Function\n","\n","**Definition:**  \n","The **objective function** in Optuna is the function that evaluates a set of hyperparameters and returns a performance score. Optuna uses this score to find the best hyperparameters.\n","\n","## Key Points\n","\n","- **Purpose:** Tell Optuna how good a model is for given hyperparameters.  \n","- **Returns:** A single value (e.g., RMSE, R²) to **minimize** or **maximize**.  \n","- **Structure:**\n","  1. Suggest hyperparameters using `trial.suggest_*`\n","  2. Train your model with these hyperparameters\n","  3. Evaluate the model on validation data\n","  4. Return the performance metric\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":12,"id":"dcb117a4","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.395014Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.3942Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.400787Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.399597Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.015689,"end_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.402815+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.387126+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["def objective(trial):\n","\n","    #hyperparameter\n","    params = {\n","         \"max_depth\" : trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 1, 10),\n","    \"min_samples_split\" : trial.suggest_int('min_samples_split', 2, 10),\n","    \"min_samples_leaf\" : trial.suggest_int('min_samples_leaf', 1, 5)}\n","\n","    #model\n","    model =  DecisionTreeRegressor(**params, random_state=42)\n","\n","    # cross-validation\n","    kf=KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n","    scores=cross_val_score(model1, X_train, y_train, cv=kf, scoring='r2')\n","\n","    return np.mean(scores)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"78b93811","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.005136,"end_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.413194+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.408058+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Optuna Trial\n","\n","**Definition:**  \n","A **Trial** in Optuna represents a **single run of the objective function** with a specific set of hyperparameters. Each trial evaluates the model and returns a score.\n","\n","## Key Points\n","\n","- **Purpose:** Track **one combination of hyperparameters** and its performance.\n","- **Hyperparameter suggestions:** Use `trial.suggest_*` methods:\n","  ```python\n","  learning_rate = trial.suggest_float(\"learning_rate\", 0.01, 0.2)\n","  max_depth = trial.suggest_int(\"max_depth\", 2, 6)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"445fe339","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.006126,"end_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.42473+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-07T18:46:17.418604+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Optuna Study\n","\n","**Definition:**  \n","A **Study** in Optuna is the **object that manages the optimization process**. It keeps track of all trials, hyperparameters tested, and their ev